The Vice President and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement expressing their sadness over the passing of James Brady. They described Brady as a dear friend and one of the country's finest public servants. They highlighted his honesty, humor, decency, and absolute courage. Brady was the press secretary to former Republican Senator Bill Roth of Delaware, and the Bidens valued their friendship with him. They also mentioned how Brady and his wife, Sarah, showed dignity, grace, and determination to turn tragedy into action after Brady was paralyzed from an assassination attempt on President Reagan. Despite his own struggles, Brady reached out to survivors of gun violence and other tragedies to offer encouragement and hope. The Bidens expressed their pride in working with Brady and Sarah in the past to advocate for commonsense efforts to prevent gun violence, and they continue to be grateful for their guidance as the nation deals with such tragedies.